<HEADLINE>
TAIWANESE ARTISTS TO JOIN FRENCH ANIMATION AND COMIC SHOW
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paris,  March 5 (CNA) 03/05/07  22:00:13 (By Lo Yuan-shao and
Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
More than 10 Taiwanese artists will join an animation and comic
show at the Festival EXIT International in Creteil, a suburb of
Paris, France March 9-17, a spokesman for the festival organizer
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The animation and comic show will be a part of the festival's
off-stage exhibitions. Both stage performances and the
exhibitions will be held at the Maison des Arts de Creteil
(Creteil Art Center) , the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Taiwanese artists joining the show include Chu Chia-juei, Tai
Chia-ming, Hung Tung-lu, Jimmy the famous illustrator, and other
artists. Taiwanese art critic Lu Jung-chi joined in planning the
animation and comics show, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Borrowing ideas from the Museum of Contemporary Art in Taipei,
and collaborating with the Shanghai Museum of Contemporary Art,
the show invited more than forty artists from Japan, Taiwan,
China, South Korea, and the Europe to show their works.
</P>
<P>
This animation and comic show will exhibit imaginative works in a
variety of forms and different media, including sculpture,
painting, porcelain, weaving, and image recording.
</P>
